Assignment API
This project is a backend service built with Node.js and Express.js, connecting to a MongoDB cloud database.
It provides an API for managing assignments, including CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.

Features
GET /api/assignments: Retrieve all assignments
GET /api/assignments/:id: Retrieve a single assignment by ID
POST /api/assignments: Create a new assignment
PUT /api/assignments: Update an existing assignment
DELETE /api/assignments/:id: Delete an assignment by ID

Prerequisites
Node.js (version 12 or later)
MongoDB Atlas account for cloud-based database setup
NPM package manager (usually comes with Node.js)

Run the server
npm start

Verify
http://localhost:8010/api/assignments

API Endpoints
Method	      Endpoint	                Description
GET	      /api/assignments	        Fetch all assignments
GET	     /api/assignments/:id     	Fetch a specific assignment by ID
POST	   /api/assignments	          Create a new assignment
PUT	    /api/assignments    	      Update an existing assignment
DELETE	/api/assignments/:id	      Delete an assignment by ID
